Credit and GPA Requirement for Team Members
How to Receive an Audition Invitation
Option One – Submit a Qualifying Video
paragraphs: The official dance team of Angelo State!

We would love to have you as part of our dance family! Our program features dynamic dancers with a variety of backgrounds. Connect with Head CoachLauren Whiteto schedule a personalized campus visit and Q&A session with current members of the team.
Angelettes perform during all home and select away football games and men’s and women’s basketball games, as well as at local and out-of-town appearances and recruitment events, and much more.

All eligible dancers receive an annual academic scholarship of up to $1,000, and any current or incoming student meeting the criteria is welcome to attend an interest clinic or submit a qualifying video for consideration.(You must receive an invitation to attend auditions by participating in one of the invitational clinics or submitting a qualifying video.)

*If you are selected for the Angelettes dance team, you may receive an academic scholarship. To qualify, members must maintain a minimum 2.0 GPA, remain in good standing with the university and team, and abide by all requirements outlined in the Angelettes Handbook.
To qualify, current ASU students must have a cumulative GPA of 2.0 or higher at the time of auditions and be of academic full-time status in good standing with the university.
Students transferring from another college or university must have been admitted to ASU at the time of auditions and have a cumulative GPA of at least 2.0.
Incoming freshmen must have been admitted to ASU at the time of auditions.

All members who make the ASU Angelettes Dance Team must be enrolled in and complete at least 12 credit hours each semester. Each member is also expected to maintain a minimum accumulative GPA of 2.0 and be in good standing with the university while on the team. Only the ASU head dance coach may grant exceptions to the course load requirement. Any member who fails to maintain these requirements is subject to dismissal from the team.
All interested dancers must choose to either submit a qualifying videoorattend an invitational clinic to receive an invite for attending Angelettes auditions!
